column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Some remaining ice on the sides of the banks as well as dead vegetation.
column14: @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Both the left and right bank had thin ice remaining and not much flow + varied flow. Majority of the flow was in the middle more deep part of the channel. Ice pans were flowing through sporadically throughout mmt. Only one large SNR variation on left bank, heavy mud layer that was probably stirred up when walking through.  Found gas tank closed at 7:55, opened and purged for 8:00. Reconnected gas to conoflow at 8:00. Conoflow found to have bubble rate issue, continuously increased bubble rate over time. After purge water level recovered to found water level. Accubar unplugged at 8:23 to install bubbler system. Bubbler plugged in at 10:45. Bubbler was reset to DWL for 11:00. SRC can be carried back to 10:50. Record before 10:50 is invalid and should be deleted back to the previous visit. Orifice block has clearly moved since last visit, appears stable and connected now. Mid-section
